Texture comment: Fresh plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomeroporphyritic dacitic lava. Moderately vesiculated. Vesicles are elongated and oriented. Seawater-origin halite precipitated in the tiny cracks. Vesicles are lined with white color secondary minerals.
Groundmass comments: Massive, glassy- or cryptocrystalline groundmass with few plag-cpx glomerocrysts and very vesicular; Some gray precipitate/coating at outer surface.
Vesicle comments: 15% of very elongated and oriented sub-rounded vesicles. Vesicle surfaces are lined with white secondary minerals.

Texture comment: Slightly altered, massive plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomeroporphyritic dacitic lava. Moderately vesiculated. Vesicles are highly elongated and aligned. Vesicles are lined with white color secondary minerals.
Groundmass comments: Massive, micro- or cryptocrystalline groundmass with few plag-cpx glomerocrysts and very vesiclular; Some gray precipitate/coating at outer surface.
Glass preservation comment: thin layer of altered glass inside vesicles
Vesicle comments: 10 vol.% of vesicles, large ones are highly elongated, smaller ones are spherical; Vesicle surfaces are lined with secondary minerals.

Texture comment: Slightly altered, massive plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomeroporphyritic dacitic lava. larger pieces have subtle alteration halo, smaller pieces are more pervasively altered resulting in a lighter gray color.
Groundmass comments: Massive, micro- or cryptocrystalline groundmass with few plag-cpx glomerocrysts and very vesiclular; Some gray precipitate/coating at outer surface.
Glass preservation comment: thin layer of altered glass inside vesicles
Vesicle comments: 10 vol.% of vesicles, large ones are highly elongated, smaller ones are spherical; Vesicle surfaces are lined with secondary minerals.

Texture comment: Fresh plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomeroporphyritic dacitic rock or lava. Moderately vesiculated, except for one roller. Vesicles are elongated and oriented. Seawater-origin halite precipitated in the tiny cracks (sparse). Vesicles are lined with white color secondary minerals and native sulfur.
Groundmass comments: Massive, glassy- or cryptocrystalline groundmass with few plag-cpx glomerocrysts and very vesicular; some vesicles have glassy linings. Native sulfur present on fractures and some vesicles of piece #1 (0-10 cm)
Vesicle comments: 14% of very elongated and oriented sub-rounded vesicles. Vesicle surfaces are lined with secondary minerals.

Texture comment: Slightly altered, massive plagioclase-pyroxene phyric glomeroporphyritic dacitic lava. Moderately vesiculated. 2 possible xenoliths
Groundmass comments: Massive, micro- or cryptocrystalline groundmass with few plag-cpx glomerocrysts and very vesiclular; Some gray precipitate/coating at outer surface. 2 possible xenoliths (angular), one with a plag-px-mgt glomerocryst
Vesicle comments: 7 vol.% vesicles, some spherical, some irregular
